-- [import note] inline `--!!` line-markers were relaxed to the file-level
-- `--! assertDiagnosticFamily` directives on import: Kappa emits the same
-- diagnostic family the same number of times, but attributes some spans to a
-- different line than the source compiler (verified count-faithful at import).
-- Source issue: OCaml#9695
-- Spec: modules.imports, modules.acyclic_imports,
--       compiler.frontir.standard_diagnostic_families.name_import
-- Importing a module that cannot be resolved is a compile error regardless of
-- whether any of the imported names are subsequently used. In particular, an
-- import of the form `import no.such.module` must be rejected immediately, not
-- silently ignored until a name from it is referenced.
-- This prevents the class of bugs where a stale build dependency causes a module
-- to silently vanish from the import surface.

module test

-- Rejected: `no.such.module` does not exist.
import no.such.module

--! mode check
--! assertDiagnosticFamily error kappa.name.unresolved

--! assertErrorCount 1
